eheh he wasn't in Mighty Ducks...

"Joseph Charles Nemec - The Fourth" or as he is known to his friends "Corky" or "Corin", plays a character on Stargate called "Jonas Quinn", who comes from a world that is about how Earth was during WW2, who have just discovered their Goa'uld heritage, and are experimenting with nuclear technology based on alien materials they found in their version of "Egypt". Jonas Quinn is almost identical to the Daniel Jackson in his beliefs, and is the moral voice of the science/military institution which is much like 'Area 51' on his planet. He hit it off with Danny in the second last episode of Season 5, and is (rumored?) to be Daniel's replacement on SG-1 in Season 6, following Daniel's ascension (yeah big spoiler - i don't give a toss anymore) and Jonas' betrayal of his superiors, after which he sought refuge at the SGC.
